[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(13) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "And Aaron was separated.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Aaron and his sons, as priests, are thus excluded from present consideration. They form the proper subject of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Chronicles 25:1-19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and are only mentioned here for the sake of completeness in the reckoning.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That he should sanctify the most holy-things.—Rather, to hallow (or consecrate) him as most holy; literally, holy of holies (qôdesh qŏdāshîm), an expression not applied to Aaron in any other passage of Scripture. The meaning is that the priests represented a higher grade of holiness, a more thorough consecration, than the mere Levites, because they were called to the discharge of a higher and holier ministry.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "That he should sanctify the most holy-things.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Rather, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "to hallow",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (or ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "consecrate",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ")",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": " him as most holy;",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " literally, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "holy of holies",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "qôdesh qŏdāshîm",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ")",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": ",",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " an expression not applied to Aaron in any other passage of Scripture. The meaning is that the priests represented a higher grade of holiness, a more thorough consecration, than the mere Levites, because they were called to the discharge of a higher and holier ministry.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "He and his sons.—All the priests are included with Aaron.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "He and his sons.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—All the priests are included with Aaron.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To burn incense.—The Hebrew term means to burn victims as well as incense.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "To burn incense.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—The Hebrew term means to burn victims as well as incense.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To minister unto him, and to bless in his name—The same words occur (Deuteronomy 10:8) with reference to the purpose for which the tribe of Levi was “separated.” The tribe obviously includes the Aaronite clan. (Comp. also Deuteronomy 21:5.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "To minister unto him, and to bless in his name",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—The same words occur (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 10:8",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ") with reference to the purpose for which the tribe of Levi was “separated.” The tribe obviously includes the Aaronite clan. (Comp. also ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 21:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".)",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And to bless in his name.—This appears right from Numbers 6:23. Others render, and to bless His name.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "And to bless in his name.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—This appears right from ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 6:23",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". Others render, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "and to bless His name.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
