  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The sons of Amram; Aaron and Moses,.... A son of Kohath, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 23:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and Aaron was separated; from the children of Israel, Exodus 28:1, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and Aaron was separated; from the children of Israel, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Exodus 28:1",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that he should sanctify the most holy things, he and his sons for ever; by an holy use of them, and keeping them from all unholy and profane uses; and this they were to do as long as the Aaronic priesthood lasted: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to burn incense before the Lord; in the holy place, on the altar of incense; which none but priests descended from Aaron might do: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to minister unto him; both at the altar of burnt offering and of incense; and the high priest in the holy of holies: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and to bless his name for ever, or \"in his name\"; that is, the people in his name; see Numbers 6:23. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and to bless his name for ever, or \"in his name\"; that is, the people in his name; see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 6:23",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Geneva Study Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cverse2",
        "text": "The sons of Amram; Aaron and Moses: and Aaron was separated, that he should {a} sanctify the most holy things, he and his sons for ever, to burn incense before the LORD, to minister unto him, and to bless in his name for ever.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "The sons of Amram; Aaron and Moses: and Aaron was separated, that he should ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{a}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " sanctify the most holy things, he and his sons for ever, to burn incense before the LORD, to minister unto him, and to bless in his name for ever.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(a) That is, to serve in the most holy place, and to consecrate the holy things.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 13.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The sons of Amram",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". From Amram, the first-mentioned son of Kohath, come the two great names of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Aaron and Moses",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 6:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Aaron was separated,...  and his sons for ever",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This statement must be read, both with ver. 3 - into the number of Levites mentioned in which Aaron and his sons do not count - and with ver. 14, which implies that Moses and his sons did count into that number. The sons of Aaron are dealt with in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 24:1-19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "infra. That he should sanctify the most holy things",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "infra. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cmt_word",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "That he should sanctify the most holy things",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The Hebrew text renders it doubtful whether the rendering here should not rather be, \"Aaron was separated to sanctify ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as most holy,\" etc. If it be so, this is the only place where the forcible term, \"holy of holies\" (most holy), is used of Aaron. The duties of the priest are described as threefold, in this place, viz.: \"to burn incense before the Lord,\" - this will carry the idea of making atonement; \"to minister to God,\" on behalf of man, ? this will be one part of the work of a mediator; and \"to bless in the Name of God,\"  - this will fulfil the remaining part. For ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "ever.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The proviso may, no doubt, include reference to the \"ever-living High Priest.\" The threefold summary of solemn and beneficent duties receives ample illustration from many passages, and in special connection with the names of Aaron and his sons (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 28:1, 38, 43",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 29:1, 35, 45",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 30:7-10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 6:22-27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). 1 Chronicles 23:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
